<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd" [ <!ENTITY rsquo "’"> <!ENTITY ndash "–"> ] ><html  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:ac="http://www.atlassian.com/schema/confluence/4/ac/" xmlns:ri="http://www.atlassian.com/schema/confluence/4/ri/" xml:lang="en" lang="en"><head><title>Orphan System (Dictionary Entry)</title></head><body><h1 style="text-align: center;"><strong><span style="color: rgb(76,154,255);">Orphan System</span></strong></h1><h2>Alternative Forms</h2><ul><li><p>Orphan</p></li></ul><h2>Definitions</h2><h3>Definition 1 <code>IT Service Management</code></h3><p>An IT system without a system owner.</p><h2>Notes</h2><p>Because nobody is responsible for an <em>orphan system</em>, the satisfaction of system requirements is no longer assured. This represent an operational risk, including a security risk.</p><h2>Related Terms</h2><ul><li><p><ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:content-title="Orphan (Dictionary Entry)" ri:version-at-save="5" /><ac:link-body>Orphan (Dictionary Entry)</ac:link-body></ac:link> </p></li><li><p><a href="https://open-measure.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DIC/pages/1004961963?search_id=ae11927e-ff6c-45df-af8d-26c57376ff39" data-card-appearance="inline">https://open-measure.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/DIC/pages/1004961963?search_id=ae11927e-ff6c-45df-af8d-26c57376ff39</a> </p></li></ul><h2>Quotes</h2><blockquote><p>It is the responsibility of the information security manager to ensure that, in the assignment process, there are no &ldquo;orphan&rdquo; systems or systems without policy-compliance owners.</p></blockquote><p style="text-align: right;">(<ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:space-key="BIB" ri:content-title="ISACA, 2012" ri:version-at-save="1" /><ac:link-body>ISACA, 2012</ac:link-body></ac:link>, p. 175)</p><h2>Bibliography</h2><ul><li><p><ac:link ac:card-appearance="inline"><ri:page ri:space-key="BIB" ri:content-title="ISACA, 2012" ri:version-at-save="1" /><ac:link-body>ISACA, 2012</ac:link-body></ac:link> </p></li></ul><h2>See Also</h2><ac:structured-macro ac:name="contentbylabel" ac:schema-version="4" data-layout="default" ac:macro-id="5e06557c-ccd0-452d-91f0-1bef4e268292"><ac:parameter ac:name="showLabels">false</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="sort">title</ac:parameter><ac:parameter ac:name="cql">label = &quot;orphan-system&quot;</ac:parameter></ac:structured-macro></body></html>